	n : Diclofenac Sodium 1% Topical
	Indications : Rheumatoid arthritis, Osteoarthritis, Joint and muscular pains
	Doses and administration : Gel: For external use only. Depending on the size of area to be treated, 2-4 g of  Gel should be applied to the skin 3-4 times daily. To the affected area gel should be rubbed in lightly.  
									Gel may also be given in addition to further treatment with other dosage forms of Diclofenac.
									
									
